 Find the slope of the tangent lines </think> Let the slope of the lines be m. Substituting $y = mx + c$ into the equation of the ellipse, we get:
${x^2 - 2x\left( {mx + c} \right) + 3{{\left( {mx + c} \right)}^2} - 5 = 0} \Rightarrow {{ - 2m{x^2} - \left( {2m - 3} \right)x - 5} = 0}$
Which is essentially a depressed quadratic whose discriminant we set equal to zero:
${\left( {2m - 3} \right)^2} - 4\left( { - 2m} \right)\left( { - 5} \right) = 0} \Rightarrow {{m^2} - 3m - {5} = 0}$
Which gives $m = \frac{3}{2}$ or $m = - 1$. The perpendiculars are:
${y = \frac{3}{2}x \\ y = - 1x}$
